---
description: Prefer explicit, strongly-typed domain models over loose types
alwaysApply: true
---

# Strong Typing

- Model the domain with explicit types (e.g. `Bucket`, `AllocationRule`, `AllocationResult`); don't pass around loosely-shaped objects.
- Avoid untyped escape hatches (`any`, unchecked casts, implicit `any`). If a type is genuinely unknown, model it explicitly.
- Represent variants with tagged/discriminated unions (e.g. amount vs percentage) so handling is exhaustive.
- Keep types close to the core logic and reuse them across layers rather than redefining shapes.
